FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41506
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1781287881
OL,3,CNine arrested in Immigration
OL,4,CEnforcement swoop at DPD bases
OL,6,FUntil now, companies hiring gig
OL,7,Feconomy and zero-hours workers,
OL,8,Fincluding in the delivery sector, have
OL,9,Fnot legally been required to check
OL,10,Ftheir right to work.
OL,12,FThis is changing and the government is
OL,13,Fdue to publish its response to the
OL,14,FExtending the Right to Work checks to
OL,15,Fthe gig economy consultation later
OL,16,Fthis month.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/7
OL,2,W,.!" ,.!+, "-$/*%+.!+,*%/*%/*-'T(,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext PageBS-SE Eng NewsCThis DayFReg TV
FL,416,410,120,260,000,100
PN,41507
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F415A1781287881
OL,3,CNine arrested in Immigration
OL,4,CEnforcement swoop at DPD bases
OL,6,FThis means companies hiring people in
OL,7,Fthe gig economy will be legally
OL,8,Frequired to carry out checks to
OL,9,Fconfirm anyone working in their name
OL,10,Fis eligible to work in the UK.
OL,12,FThose who fail to do so will face
OL,13,Fhefty penalties including fines of up
OL,14,Fto #60,000 per worker, director
OL,15,Fdisqualifications and potential prison
OL,16,Fsentences of up to five years.
OL,18,FFrom Westminster to Washington DC -
OL,19,Four political experts are across all
OL,20,Fthe latest key talking points. Listen
OL,21,Fto the latest episode below...
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/7
